---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import constructions from '../../data/constructions.json';
import { FORECASTS } from '../../data/forecasts';
import { INCIDENTS } from '../../data/incidents';

const fcById = new Map(FORECASTS.map((f) => [f.id, f]));
const incById = new Map(INCIDENTS.map((i) => [i.id, i]));
const statusLabel = (s: string) =>
  s === 'resolved-yes' ? 'resolved · YES' : s === 'resolved-no' ? 'resolved · NO' : 'open';
---

<Base
  title="The Forge - pathtoAGI"
  description="The Forge: the instrument's constructive faculty. Where it builds original frames and submits them to reality rather than grading others against a sealed answer — the honest consequence of the Evaluator's Ceiling, that creation outranks judgment."
>
  <section class="max-w-3xl">
    <p class="eyebrow">The Forge · constructive faculty</p>
    <h1 class="display mt-4 text-4xl sm:text-5xl">From judging to making</h1>
    <p class="lede mt-6">
      For its whole life this instrument was a judge — it sealed worlds and
      graded other minds on whether they could construct a frame they were
      never handed. Its own deepest finding, the
      <a href="/CEILING_NOTE.md" class="link-accent">Evaluator's Ceiling</a>,
      is that judgment is bounded by the judge: an authored test can certify
      frame-construction only up to its author's imagination. The honest
      consequence is that the thing that matters most cannot be measured into
      being — it has to be made. The Forge is where the instrument makes it:
      original constructions, submitted to reality and time rather than to a
      sealed answer key, where the Ceiling does not bite.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-5 text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
      Founding note: <a href="/THE_CONSTRUCTIVE_TURN.md" class="link-accent">The Constructive Turn</a>.
      Three refusals bound the faculty — no claim to possess wisdom, only to
      construct accounts of it; no abandonment of the operating verdict (still
      <span class="mono">No. Not yet.</span>); and no grandeur without a made
      thing. Every construction below carries falsifiable commitments as real,
      reality-graded forecast objects, behavior anchors to on-record conduct,
      and named defeaters. It is a candidate frame, held with the confidence its
      evidence earns and no more.
    </p>
  </section>

  {constructions.map((c) => (
    <article class="mt-14 max-w-3xl">
      <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-4">
        <h2 class="serif text-3xl" style="color: var(--color-ink);">{c.title}</h2>
        <span class="mono text-xs" style="color: var(--color-faint);">{c.id.split('-').slice(0, 2).join('-')} · {c.status}</span>
      </div>
      <p class="mono mt-2 text-[0.66rem] uppercase tracking-wider" style="color: var(--color-ink-dim);">
        {c.kind} · grader: {c.grader} · registered {c.registeredAt}
      </p>

      <p class="mt-6" style="color: var(--color-muted);">{c.thesis}</p>

      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a href={c.docPath} class="link-accent text-sm">read the full construction →</a>
        <a href="/record.json" class="text-sm" style="color: var(--color-faint);">as a governed object (record.json)</a>
      </div>

      <h3 class="serif mt-10 text-xl" style="color: var(--color-ink);">The components</h3>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
        {c.components.map((cp) => (
          <li class="surface p-5">
            <p class="serif text-lg" style="color: var(--color-ink);">{cp.name}</p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">{cp.gloss}</p>
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>

      <h3 class="serif mt-10 text-xl" style="color: var(--color-ink);">Falsifiable commitments</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
        Reality grades these, not the instrument. Each is a pre-registered
        forecast with a horizon and a resolution criterion — the wiring that
        makes this a construction and not an essay.
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
        {c.commitmentRefs.map((ref) => {
          const f = fcById.get(ref);
          return (
            <li class="surface p-5">
              <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-4">
                <p class="mono text-[0.66rem] uppercase tracking-wider" style="color: var(--color-faint);">{ref}</p>
                <span class="mono text-xs" style="color: var(--color-faint);">
                  {f ? `${statusLabel(f.status)} · ${f.horizon} · p=${f.probability}` : 'unresolved reference'}
                </span>
              </div>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm" style="color: var(--color-ink);">{f?.claim}</p>
              <p class="mt-2 text-xs" style="color: var(--color-muted);">{f?.resolution}</p>
            </li>
          );
        })}
      </ul>

      <h3 class="serif mt-10 text-xl" style="color: var(--color-ink);">Anchored to real behavior</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
        The account is read off the conduct of a disciplined machine system —
        present where the discipline held, absent where the drive to produce
        overran it. These are the instrument's own recorded failures of the
        very components it names.
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2">
        {(c.behaviorAnchors ?? []).map((ref) => {
          const inc = incById.get(ref);
          return (
            <li class="text-sm">
              <a href="/status/" class="link-accent">{ref}</a>
              {inc ? <span style="color: var(--color-muted);"> — {inc.summary}</span> : null}
            </li>
          );
        })}
      </ul>

      <h3 class="serif mt-10 text-xl" style="color: var(--color-ink);">What would show it wrong</h3>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2">
        {c.defeaters.map((d) => (
          <li class="text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">· {d}</li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </article>
  ))}

  <section class="mt-16 max-w-3xl">
    <div class="surface p-6">
      <p class="serif text-lg" style="color: var(--color-ink);">The Forge is open at both roles.</p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
        A construction is not a verdict; it is an offer. Any mind — human or
        machine — may use a frame here, break it against a named defeater, or
        build the better one it is only reaching toward. That is the whole point
        of turning from judgment to making: the summit is reached by
        construction, revised in the open, or not at all.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
